Title: Champagne Bottle Picnic Tote
Body (HTML):
Fatcork co-founders Abby & Bryan Maletis pop into J.Stark, a Charleston, S.C.-based bags and leather goods shop, whenever they are down south visiting Abby's family.

Now, we’re all excited about our very own custom collaboration with the brand. The fatcork Champagne Bottle Tote by J.Stark will soon become your go-to for bringing your bubbles to all your picnics, BBQs and beach days. 

The details:

The tote features interior pockets (tailor made for your bottles of bub), exterior pockets (a perfect fit for cheese knives, Champagne stoppers and other accessories) and plenty of room for a blanket, snacks and glassware to go. 

Product details: 

    • Canvas bag in Olive color

    • Wickett & Craig English bridle leather handles

    • Collapsible bottle sleeves

    • Three-bottle capacity

    • Reinforced bottom

    • Antique brass hardware

    • Woven fatcork label

 

Disclaimer: bottles and merchandise not included

Title: 11, 12, 13 ... 20 Brut Nature
Body (HTML):
SEE: Gold with flecks of navel orange

SMELL: Hazelnut husk, orchard fruit and white flowers

TASTE: Candied lemon rind, tart acidity and notes of bruised yellow apple and baking spice

PAIR: Pour these bubbles with flakey breakfast pastries filled with custard or fruity jam, a hunk of crusty baguette with soft cheese and spiced nuts, or rich, spicy takeout from your favorite Indian restaurant.

This au naturel beauty is the product of a perpetual solera system, whereby the wine of each new vintage is added to an existing reserve. This specific cuvée is the blend of vintages 2011 through 2017 from all the domaine’s parcels.

Title: Martin-Fontaine 2019
Body (HTML):
SEE: Pale hay with a metallic glimmer and exquisite clarity

SMELL: Daffodils, green grass, sun-baked peach skins, dried apricots and golden yellow apples with a kiss of caramel and fresh-husked walnuts

TASTE: Salt water taffy, vanilla bean and toast followed by lime zest and green pear, dried stone fruits and lingering minerality

PAIR: Share this delightful Champagne alongside aged nutty, crumbly cheese, fresh figs and candied nuts. Or make it the star of your second course: fiocchetti with blue cheese, pear and crushed walnuts.

The grapes for the cuvée come from a parcel of vineyard perched at the top of a hill with sun exposure from the south and southwest. The name “Martin-Fontaine” is derived from “Mort Fontaine,” French for “dead fountain,” and refers to an old water source at the bottom of the hill. Ruppert-Leroy produces only 3,500 bottles of this cuvée each year.

Organic production. Clay-Limestone soil with a majority of white limestone. Elevage in barrels sur lie for 6 months, then 2 years in bottle ‘sur lattes’.

Title: Fosse Grely Brut Nature 2020
Body (HTML):
SEE: Golden honey with a frothy mousse 

SMELL: Red fruit, peach leaves and tuberose petals

TASTE: Bing cherry, red anjou pear followed by a burst of fresh citrus. Silky with a pronounced mineral finish.

PAIR: These bubbles shine on their own or with a light crunchy snack of seedy crackers and hard cheese. This bottle is also a knockout pairing with white fish baked in parchment with fresh herbs and lemon butter. 

Fosse-Grely is the largest parcel of their the domaine. The name "Fosse", french for ditch, and "Grely" an old regional term for gravel speak to the terroir of this plot of grapes, the first parcel to be planted back in the 1980s by Gérard, Bénédicte's father.

Each year, Ruppert-Leroy produces only 7,000 bottles of this nuanced cuvée, named after the Fosse-Grely vineyard. Squeezed from grapes grown in rich, red clay-limestone soil, the juice rests sur lie for six months in stainless steel, and it ages for an additional two years in the bottle before disgorgement.

Title: Intro to Grower Champagne
Body (HTML):
Grower Champagne is Champagne produced by the people who also grow the grapes and tend the vines, often on land passed down through the generations. It’s humble, authentic and out-of-this-world delicious. This unique gift set is the perfect way to discover why the cool crowd is asking for grower Champagne. Here’s what’s included:

  • Three deliciously distinct grower Champagnes, each with its own unique flavor profile: 
    • Mathieu-Gandon Esprit Saveur — a blend of 60% pinot noir 40% chardonnay (vinified in used oak barrels for up to five years) from the Champagne subregion Vallée de la Marne
    • Didier-Ducos Absolu Meunier — 100% pinot meunier from the Champagne subregion Vallée de la Marne. One of the three major grape varieties grown in Champagne, pinot meunier has long been used in blends. Now, thanks to growers like Didier-Ducos, it is gaining popularity on its own. 
    • Gimonnet-Oger Blanc de Blancs — 100% chardonnay that has been aged to perfection. This is a traditional and delightful representation of blanc de blancs from the chalky soils of Champagne’s Côte des Blancs subregion.
Plus …
  • The best-ever ice bag
  • The perfect bottle stopper
  • Intro to Grower Champagne Booklet

Title: Blanc de Blancs 2017
Body (HTML):
This cuvée is one of two new additions to the Mathieu-Gandon portfolio, and fatcork fans are the first to try it. The chardonnay grapes for this stunning vintage are from parcels that Séverine recently inherited from her grandfather in Verzy. During fermentation, 10 percent of the juice ferments in used oak, while 80 percent hangs out in stainless steel. Mathieu-Gandon produces only 1,500 bottles annually.

SEE:  Warm spring sunshine, beautiful clarity, fervent-yet-elegant bubbles and frothy mousse

SMELL: Sweet green vegetal notes, yellow apple, mineral notes and white floral aromas

TASTE: Fresh and vibrant with notes of just-cut grass, sweet peas, sourdough bread and clotted cream. Beautiful structure in the midpalate with present acidity and a long, lingering, mineral finish.

PAIR: Try these bubbles with mild blue cheese and fresh grapes, grilled white fish topped with herbs and lemon or delicate angel hair pasta with seasonal vegetables and butter sauce.  

CELEBRATE: Your boss surprised you today with the best news: The promotion she’d been working on pushing through for you was finally approved, and you’re the team’s newest senior manager. Cheers to your hard work and coworkers in your corner.

Title: Special Club Millésime 2016 Nature

SMELL: Toasted almond and ripe notes of  apple and pear

TASTE: A supple mouthfeel with balanced notes of lemon curd, orchard fruit, vanilla bean, and citrus rind. Juicy at first with zesty minerality in the mid-palate and a long, clean finish.

PAIR: This cuvée expertly complements a selection of firm cheeses and smoked meats, but it can also round out a lobster dinner featuring baked potatoes and stuffed mushrooms. Mmm.

Title: Un R de Folie Magnum
Body (HTML):
Like us, you may have fallen in love with Adrien Redon’s petal pink L’R du Temps Rosé or his perfectly balanced Un R d’Autrefois Extra Brut, but you’ve never tasted anything quite like the domaine’s first-ever magnum — Un R de Folie. This limited edition large-format Champagne is a complex, fruit-forward ode to Adrien Redon’s big, creative family.

While the Champagne itself is a Redon labor of brotherly love, its label features an abstract representation of the domaine’s terroir painted by Adrien’s mother, Pascale. The bottle also includes a crystal medallion created by the youngest Redon and master glassblower, Valentin. 

Made with 100 percent 2015 chardonnay from a single parcel, Adrien’s release of 328 large-format bottles features citrus notes followed by vanilla and a pinch of biscuit that pairs beautifully with hors d'oeuvres like gougères and salmon rillettes or at the table with rabbit terrine.

Tags: ABV-12, Bottle Size_Large Format, Grower_A. Levasseur, Inventory, REGION-VALLÉE DE LA MARNE, Single Bottles, Style_Blanc des Noirs, Style_Vintage, VINTAGE-100% 2018, VINTAGE-BASE 2018

Title: Millésime 2018 Premier Cru
Body (HTML):
SEE: Gold and straw yellow 

SMELL: Fresh lemon, butter, honeysuckle and thyme followed by lemongrass, candied pineapple and coffee mocha

TASTE: Warm brioche, marshmallow, white florals and tart yeasty notes. Structured and weighty with present acidity and chalky minerality. 

PAIR: Enjoy this cuvée with a spread of aged crumbly cheeses, Spanish pimentón almonds, salty meats and seedy crackers. Or drink it with grilled cheese and ripe tomato on sourdough.

The youngest cuvée in our new bundle, Millésime 2018 Premier Cru features chardonnay grapes that were put through their paces. An exceptionally rainy winter, a very mild spring and  extreme summer heat, drought and sunshine produced a large quantity of fruit and plenty of top-quality musts for the cellar. These conditions were wholly suited to Jean Luc’s old-school approach of minimal intervention during the fermentation process. He refrains from controlling the temperature and uses old, wooden tanks that allow the wine to breathe.

Title: Clos des Maladries
Body (HTML):
SEE: Straw-like yellow with hints of green around the edges and spritzy effervescence. 

SMELL: Green apple, pear and quince. Perhaps a squeeze of lime and a dash of salt.

TASTE: Almond, honeycomb and sliced orchard fruit. Sharp, precise and linear in structure with a plush and silky mouthfeel that lingers.

PAIR: Pop this bottle with a fancy dinner starring roast duck, or pair it with a black truffle bagel smeared with cream cheese and topped with smoked salmon and fresh dill.

The walled-in Clos des Maladries vineyard sits at the border of Avize behind Etienne’s ancestral home. These vines were planted by Etienne’s grandfather in the 1970s. Plowed by horse and bottled as a single vintage each year, this Grand Cru cuvée is a representation of prime terroir. The name “Les Maladries” has roots in the Middle Ages when the area was used to house those who had fallen sick with the plague.

* There is a purchase limit of 1 bottle per customer. This bottle is special, rare, and in limited supply.

Title: Champagne & Caviar | 7:45 to 8:45 PM | Session 2
Body (HTML):
Join us for an evening of bubbles and caviar at the fatcork cave!

Fatcork is incredibly excited to announce a fresh event partnership with local Seattle business Ebb&Co.! 

Ebb&Co is a gathering space focused on bringing the community together around the table. They collaborate with chefs, winemakers, fishermen, farmers and makers to create dinners, classes and events celebrating natural wine and seasonal, local foods. 

Stephanie Eburah, who runs this beautiful little shop, also happens to be former culinary director, and current ambassador of California Caviar Company. They’ve got the serious goods, and we can’t wait to share.

We will be pairing a number of tasty caviar bumps with select cuvées for a tasting experience that is likely to blow minds and drop jaws. Here’s the deets:

Included in ticket price: 

  • A taste of six different fatcork Champagnes
  • A taste of six different types of Caviar
  • Caviar spoon to take home with you after the tasting
  • Fatcork Champagne stopper

***There is also a Champagne and Caviar Tasting at Ebb&Co. on December 10th from 6-8 PM. Tickets for that event are hosted on the Ebb&Co website.

Title: Dosage from Zero to Brut (3 bottles)
Body (HTML):
Nature, Extra Brut, Brut. Oh my!

Have you ever looked at a bottle of bubbly and asked yourself, "What's the difference between extra brut and brut?" Or, "What the heck is brut nature?" In this kit, you will discover all about the sweetness scale of Champagne and how the mixture of sugar and reserve wine, aka dosage, added at the last step of the process determines the style of Champagne.  

Included:

Title: Absolue Grès Brut Nature
Body (HTML):
SEE: Amber with flecks of gold

SMELL: Red plum, citrus zest and white florals 

TASTE: Plum and citrus. Powerful in structure with dense flavors balanced by fresh acidity. Dry, satisfying finish. 

PAIR: Pour yourself a glass, and leave the bottle open while you throw juicy spot prawns on the grill. You’ll notice how the Champagne changes as it’s left to take in air. 

While most of Elise Dechannes’ vineyards enjoy southeastern sun exposure on the steep hillsides of Les Riceys, the pinot noir grapes that Elise uses to make this stunning limited-release cuvée come from the old-vine parcel Val Preuse, which is mostly flat. French for “sandstone,” Grès achieves its signature freshness through vinification in sandstone amphora. Leave this bottle open as you sip, and notice how the dense plum and citrus flavors change as the Champagne takes in air.

* There is a purchase limit of 2 bottles per customer. This cuvée is special, rare, and in limited supply.

Title: Les Grains Blancs Brut Nature
Body (HTML):
Hervieux-Dumez created this “nature” version of their blanc de blancs exclusively  for fatcork! You might notice that it’s slightly more tart than the original cuvée with more pronounced notes of fresh green herbs.

SEE: Bright yellow with flecks of gold, delicate beads and a fluffy mousse 

SMELL: Fresh green grass, honeydew melon and blooming daffodil 

TASTE: Elegant and refreshing with notes of yellow flowers, marzipan, vanilla and warm biscuits.

PAIR: Pop this bottle to enjoy with a “pick-and-peck,” featuring grainy crackers, crumbly hard cheese, fresh fruit, cold roasted chicken, crudités and dijonaise for dunking.

Title: Les Grains Blancs Brut
Body (HTML):
SEE: The color of diffuse sunlight. Delicate beads and a fluffy mousse. 

SMELL: Baking flour, honeysuckle and camomile

TASTE: Cantaloupe, lemon drop candy, white tea and a dip into savory territory thanks to a green note of pea tendrils or raw asparagus. A silky and smooth mouthfeel with balanced acidity. 

PAIR: This Champagne goes with warm, salted popcorn as well as with richer dishes like shrimp and grits with cured bacon or a bubbly croque monsieur.  It’s also a beautiful companion for an omelet stuffed with gruyère and fresh herbs or quiche Lorraine.

Title: Blanc de Blancs Millésime 2012 Premier Cru
Body (HTML):
SEE: Warm golden tones in the glass bounce merrily around the glass. Fat golden pearls rise into a soft mousse.

SMELL: Bubbles are small and soft as they snap under tongue, and dissipate quickly. Seductive citrus gives way to flakey brioche, and warm honey. A light blanket of pleasant must alludes to years of age.

TASTE: Cashmere-like texture on the palate—smooth, delicate, rich. Maturity from age on the lees is still balanced by super fresh notes fresh churned butter, flakey crust and lemon zest. Bright and tart notes sliced green apple come through in the end. Expect a lively and fresh finish.

The 2012 vintage in Champagne withstood its share of unwieldy weather. But the frantic succession of winter and spring frosts, torrential rains, hailstorms, a cold snap, intense heat and drought in the vineyards belonging to Gimonnet-Oger brought forth the extraordinary Blanc de Blancs Millésime 2012 Premier Cru, and elegant, racy cuvée endowed with a beautiful, sapid complexity. This subtle, almost austere version of blanc de blancs has just come of age in Jean Luc’s cellar, and it’s ready to pop today.
Product Category: Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Alcoholic Beverages > Wine

Title: Millésime 2008 La Guette 1er Cru
Body (HTML):
SEE: Metallic gold 

SMELL: Classic pear and baked apple with nutty notes and a shave of lemon zest

TASTE: Shortbread, butter cookies and candied caramel with fresh acidity, minerality and white floral notes

PAIR: This bottle plays well with a rustic snack of roasted vegetables, thinly sliced jamón and hard, crumbly cheeses. Or pair it with Filipino Spanish bread to complement the snack’s sweet buttery filling.

A tribute to Jean Luc’s patient, reserved approach to Champagne-making, his Millésime 2008 La Guette Premier Cru has just finally reached maturity. Complex, elegant and finely mineral, it offers a snapshot of 2008 in Champagne. A classic cool, rainy spring followed by summer storms and a cool, windy fall led the grapes through a slow and gentle ripening, which resulted in fine, fresh wine with structure. Jean Luc made this particular cuvée with grapes from the “La Guette,” a plot in the Premier Cru village of Cuis.

Title: Premier Cru Extra Brut Réserve
Body (HTML):
When making this special cuvée, Laureen Baillette found the right balance at 4 g/l which is half her standard dosage. This custom Champagne is an even split between the three major grapes of the region, and 50 percent is a perpetual réserve, which brings beautiful structure and great length in the finish. The blend’s 10 percent chardonnay has been aged in used oak barrels, adding a distinct level of complexity, depth and length of finish to this harmonious blend.

SEE: Clear, luminous, effervescent and unmistakably Premier Cru. Frothy golden bubbles rise in regular streams and form a full bead on the surface.

SMELL: Red apple skin, juicy red currant and doughy brioche followed by a bouquet of white flowers

TASTE: Ripe fruit and white flowers. Delicate effervescence. Beautiful acidity bursts mid-palate offering contrast to the round, rich mouthfeel. 

PAIR: Pop this bottle pre-meal as an apéritif or with a bonafide feast starring a roasted ham dressed in fresh herbs.

We’re all about the dirty details. 

Champagne’s diversity of terroir is, in a word, exquisite. What was once an ancient ocean is now the dried-up marine bed of the Paris Basin. The soil here is rich in nutrients and minerals, and Champagnes from each of these regions are uniquely expressive of the land from which they come. Take a tour of terroir and explore a bottle from each sub region.

Title: Brut Tradition Premier Cru Jeroboam
Body (HTML):
Green reflections dance at the edges of this bright-yellow wine with calm, fine bubbles. 

Right away, you’ll recognize it as a chardonnay-dominated cuvée, thanks to floral, green apple, and marshmallow aromas. After a few seconds, you might pick up mineral notes and anise. Allow it to aerate a few minutes so you can smell developing notes of toast, melted butter, honey, and warm grapefruit. 

Fresh with good acidity and zero bitterness, the wine grows rounder as it moves across the palate.
